The guiding topics for the sessions were divided as follows:
Investment models of multilateral development banks for local manufacturing of health products;
Reflections on capital expenditure and operating expense (CAPEX-OPEX) models and estimated capacity to contribute to a pandemic response within the context of the mRNA Technology Transfer Programme;
Building the ecosystem for development of new mRNA-based products in LMICs;
Addressing the needs of a nascent mRNA industry in LMICs;
Envisaging new financing models for LMIC-based manufacturers (Table S2).
